{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gzweb/issues/66/comments/53243600.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gzweb/issues/66#comment-53243600"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gzweb/issues/66.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 66, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gzweb.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gzweb"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3e2fc3f2-dc25-453b-9792-943c743d9b40}ts=1609263"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gzweb", "full_name": "osrf/gzweb", "uuid": "{3e2fc3f2-dc25-453b-9792-943c743d9b40}"}, "title": "Configurable cameraview init pose"}, "content": {"raw": "Looks like this is some sort of race condition which resets the camera position to zero in the init; even though `resetView()` is called. Current work around for this would be adding `this.resetView();` at the end of the `GZ3D.Scene.prototype.init` method \\(approx line 5562\\) in `gz3d.js`", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Looks like this is some sort of race condition which resets the camera position to zero in the init; even though <code>resetView()</code> is called. Current work around for this would be adding <code>this.resetView();</code> at the end of the <code>GZ3D.Scene.prototype.init</code> method (approx line 5562) in <code>gz3d.js</code></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-08-01T13:55:44.966475+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Ansar Khan", "uuid": "{3ff227d6-5bfd-442d-a735-d48b0eee7786}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3ff227d6-5bfd-442d-a735-d48b0eee7786%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3ff227d6-5bfd-442d-a735-d48b0eee7786%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/68874b8d9f304c07d0d47cffb3109dc3d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsAK-6.png"}}, "nickname": "Ansar Khan", "type": "user", "account_id": "5d42ece0f14e7c0da562bf44"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id"